<emphasis id="B90A064AFF9CFFD0FEA8FE6B0EC3FE62" box="[264,483,433,458]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Historical account</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36489D3FF9CFFD0FE98FE030EDEF8EB" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC1DA58FF9CFFD0FE98FE030E4DFD4B" blockId="8.[264,1324,433,1859]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
After the description of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C7EA1DBFF9CFFD0FD6EFE030CD4FE5B" authority="Ehrenberg" authorityName="Ehrenberg" box="[718,1012,473,499]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Heterometrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90A064AFF9CFFD0FD6EFE030C4EFE5A" box="[718,878,473,498]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Heterometrus</emphasis>
Ehrenberg
</taxonomicName>
, several new species were added by other authors. The first attempted revision was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEFA7A9FF9CFFD0FBF3FDDB0A25FDB3" author="Pocock" box="[1107,1285,513,539]" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" refString="Pocock, R. I. (1900) The scorpions of the genus Heterometrus. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, (7) 5, 362 - 365." type="journal article" year="1900">
Pocock (
<number id="3DB6C87FFF9CFFD0FB1CFDDB0BDCFDB3" box="[1212,1276,513,539]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1900.0">1900</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. In this he defined several primary characters for the identification of the species. More recently, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEFA7A9FF9CFFD0FED5FD8B0D09FDC3" author="Couzijn" box="[373,553,593,619]" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" refString="Couzijn, H. W. C. (1981) Revision of the genus Heterometrus Hemprich and Ehrenberg (Scorpionidae, Arachnidea). Zoologische Verhandelingen, 184, 1 - 196." type="journal article" year="1981">
Couzijn (
<number id="3DB6C87FFF9CFFD0FE44FD8B0D01FDC3" box="[484,545,593,619]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1981.0">1981</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
proposed a complete monographic revision, including results of his dissertation with detailed keys. Next, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEFA7A9FF9CFFD0FD5AFDA30B4AFD3B" author="Tikader" box="[762,1130,633,659]" pageId="8" pageNumber="16" refString="Tikader, B. K. &amp; Bastawade, D. B. (1983) The Fauna of India. Vol. 3. Scorpions (Scorpionida: Arachnida). Zoological Survey of India, Calcutta, 671 pp." type="book" year="1983">
Tikader and Bastawade (
<number id="3DB6C87FFF9CFFD0FB84FDA30B41FD3B" box="[1060,1121,633,659]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1983.0">1983</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
published redescriptions and keys for the Indian scorpion fauna, and described two new species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7EA1DBFF9CFFD0FB7EFD7B0E46FD4A" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Heterometrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90A064AFF9CFFD0FB7EFD7B0E46FD4A" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Heterometrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC1DA58FF9CFFD0FE98FD2B0D07FABB" blockId="8.[264,1324,433,1859]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
At the beginning of this study we attempted to use the monograph of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEFA7A9FF9CFFD0FBFCFD2B0A2EFCA3" author="Couzijn" box="[1116,1294,753,779]" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" refString="Couzijn, H. W. C. (1981) Revision of the genus Heterometrus Hemprich and Ehrenberg (Scorpionidae, Arachnidea). Zoologische Verhandelingen, 184, 1 - 196." type="journal article" year="1981">
Couzijn (
<number id="3DB6C87FFF9CFFD0FB68FD2B0A25FCA3" box="[1224,1285,753,779]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1981.0">1981</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
to compare and identify the material from Chinese Tibet. Our analysis lead us to the species 
<taxonomicName id="4C7EA1DBFF9CFFD0FEA8FC9B0CDCFCF3" authority="Couzijn, 1981" authorityName="Couzijn" authorityYear="1981" box="[264,1020,833,859]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Heterometrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fastigiosus" subGenus="Chersonesometrus">
<emphasis id="B90A064AFF9CFFD0FEA8FC9B0E88FCF2" box="[264,424,833,858]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Heterometrus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B90A064AFF9CFFD0FE64FC9B0DBEFCF2" box="[452,670,833,858]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Chersonesometrus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B90A064AFF9CFFD0FD1AFC9B0C17FCF2" box="[698,823,833,858]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">fastigiosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFEFA7A9FF9CFFD0FCE9FC9B0CDCFCF3" author="Couzijn" box="[841,1020,833,859]" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" refString="Couzijn, H. W. C. (1981) Revision of the genus Heterometrus Hemprich and Ehrenberg (Scorpionidae, Arachnidea). Zoologische Verhandelingen, 184, 1 - 196." type="journal article" year="1981">
Couzijn, 
<number id="3DB6C87FFF9CFFD0FC1FFC9B0CDCFCF3" box="[959,1020,833,859]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1981.0">1981</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, described from Indian Himalaya, but which was also thought to exist in 
<collectingCountry id="F3699AC8FF9CFFD0FCE9FCB30CB3FC2B" box="[841,915,873,899]" name="Nepal" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Nepal</collectingCountry>
. The male 
<typeStatus id="54C564FAFF9CFFD0FBB2FCB30B59FC2B" box="[1042,1145,873,899]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<collectionCode id="ED6F429DFF9CFFD0FB28FCB30BE4FC2B" LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34838" box="[1160,1220,873,899]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34838" name="Forschungsinstitut und Natur-Museum Senckenberg" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">SMF</collectionCode>
<collectionCode id="ED6F429DFF9CFFD0FB6CFCB30BFFFC2B" box="[1228,1247,873,899]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">II</collectionCode>
/ 
<number id="3DB6C87FFF9CFFD0FB47FCB30A01FC2B" box="[1255,1313,873,899]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="8886.0">8886</number>
/ 
<number id="3DB6C87FFF9CFFD0FEA8FC4B0E15FC03" box="[264,309,913,939]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="228.0">228</number>
) and two female 
<typeStatus id="54C564FAFF9CFFD0FDAAFC4B0D5AFC03" box="[522,634,913,939]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">paratypes</typeStatus>
(MNHN­RS­0123, 0145) of this last species were examined by one of us (
<collectionCode id="ED6F429DFF9CFFD0FE7FFC630D04FC7B" box="[479,548,953,979]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/en0m-p9xn" name="The Wellcome Bacterial Collection" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">WRL</collectionCode>
) and noticeable differences were observed between it and the new species. We also realized that most characters proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEFA7A9FF9CFFD0FC44FC3B0BBBFC53" author="Couzijn" box="[996,1179,993,1019]" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" refString="Couzijn, H. W. C. (1981) Revision of the genus Heterometrus Hemprich and Ehrenberg (Scorpionidae, Arachnidea). Zoologische Verhandelingen, 184, 1 - 196." type="journal article" year="1981">
Couzijn (
<number id="3DB6C87FFF9CFFD0FBF6FC3B0BB3FC53" box="[1110,1171,993,1019]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1981.0">1981</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
were completely inadequate for precise identification. A new revision of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C7EA1DBFF9CFFD0FB2BFBD30A0BFB8A" box="[1163,1323,1033,1058]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Heterometrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90A064AFF9CFFD0FB2BFBD30A0BFB8A" box="[1163,1323,1033,1058]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Heterometrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was published by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEFA7A9FF9CFFD0FE7BFBEB0DB4FBE3" author="Kovarik" box="[475,660,1073,1099]" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" refString="Kovarik, F. (2004) A review of the genus Heterometrus Ehrenberg, 1828, with descriptions of seven new species (Scorpiones, Scorpionidae). Euscorpius, 15, 1 - 60." type="journal article" year="2004">
Kovařík (
<number id="3DB6C87FFF9CFFD0FDEBFBEB0DACFBE3" box="[587,652,1073,1099]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Among other taxonomic decisions, this author regarded 
<taxonomicName id="4C7EA1DBFF9CFFD0FEA8FB830EC0FBDA" box="[264,480,1113,1139]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Heterometrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fastigiosus" subGenus="Chersonesometrus">
<emphasis id="B90A064AFF9CFFD0FEA8FB830E3DFBDA" box="[264,285,1113,1138]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">H</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="B90A064AFF9CFFD0FE96FB830E69FBDA" box="[310,329,1113,1138]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">C</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="B90A064AFF9CFFD0FEC3FB830EC0FBDA" box="[355,480,1113,1138]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">fastigiosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7EA1DBFF9CFFD0FD61FB830BF8FBDB" authority="C.L. Koch, 1841" authorityName="C.L. Koch" authorityYear="1841" box="[705,1240,1113,1139]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Heterometrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bengalensis">
<emphasis id="B90A064AFF9CFFD0FD61FB830CD4FBDA" box="[705,1012,1113,1138]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Heterometrus bengalensis</emphasis>
(C.L. Koch, 
<number id="3DB6C87FFF9CFFD0FB31FB830BEFFBDB" box="[1169,1231,1113,1139]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1841.0">1841</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, a species usually distributed further to the south of 
<collectingCountry id="F3699AC8FF9CFFD0FCC5FB5B0C85FB33" box="[869,933,1153,1179]" name="India" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">India</collectingCountry>
. Seven new species were also described. The examination of the male 
<typeStatus id="54C564FAFF9CFFD0FD4DFB730C73FB6B" box="[749,851,1193,1219]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7EA1DBFF9CFFD0FCDFFB730B7AFB6A" box="[895,1114,1193,1219]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Heterometrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fastigiosus" subGenus="Chersonesometrus">
<emphasis id="B90A064AFF9CFFD0FCDFFB730CB4FB6A" box="[895,916,1193,1218]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">H</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="B90A064AFF9CFFD0FC0FFB730CE2FB6A" box="[943,962,1193,1218]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">C</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="B90A064AFF9CFFD0FC7DFB730B7AFB6A" box="[989,1114,1193,1218]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">fastigiosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed that the specimen was in fact a female. Apparently 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEFA7A9FF9CFFD0FCABFB0B0CE1FB43" author="Kovarik" box="[779,961,1233,1259]" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" refString="Kovarik, F. (2004) A review of the genus Heterometrus Ehrenberg, 1828, with descriptions of seven new species (Scorpiones, Scorpionidae). Euscorpius, 15, 1 - 60." type="journal article" year="2004">
Kovařík (
<number id="3DB6C87FFF9CFFD0FCDBFB0B0C99FB43" box="[891,953,1233,1259]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
was not aware of this mistake done by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEFA7A9FF9CFFD0FECDFB230D03FABB" author="Couzijn" box="[365,547,1273,1299]" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" refString="Couzijn, H. W. C. (1981) Revision of the genus Heterometrus Hemprich and Ehrenberg (Scorpionidae, Arachnidea). Zoologische Verhandelingen, 184, 1 - 196." type="journal article" year="1981">
Couzijn (
<number id="3DB6C87FFF9CFFD0FE7AFB230D39FABB" box="[474,537,1273,1299]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1981.0">1981</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC1DA58FF9CFFD0FE98FAFB0EFFF9FB" blockId="8.[264,1324,433,1859]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
We agree with Kovařík’s (
<number id="3DB6C87FFF9CFFD0FDC9FAFB0D87FA93" box="[617,679,1313,1339]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2004.0">2004</number>
) opinion of the usefulness of the characters selected by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEFA7A9FF9CFFD0FEA8FA930EE0FACB" author="Couzijn" box="[264,448,1353,1379]" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" refString="Couzijn, H. W. C. (1981) Revision of the genus Heterometrus Hemprich and Ehrenberg (Scorpionidae, Arachnidea). Zoologische Verhandelingen, 184, 1 - 196." type="journal article" year="1981">
Couzijn (
<number id="3DB6C87FFF9CFFD0FEDAFA930E97FACB" box="[378,439,1353,1379]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1981.0">1981</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
to define the species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7EA1DBFF9CFFD0FD5BFA930CBBFACA" box="[763,923,1353,1378]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Heterometrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90A064AFF9CFFD0FD5BFA930CBBFACA" box="[763,923,1353,1378]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Heterometrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Moreover Kovařík’ decision to place the different subgenera of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7EA1DBFF9CFFD0FD21FAAB0C01FA22" box="[641,801,1393,1418]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Heterometrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90A064AFF9CFFD0FD21FAAB0C01FA22" box="[641,801,1393,1418]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Heterometrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within a single nominal genus seems to be a step in the right direction. However, the rest of Kovařík’ (
<number id="3DB6C87FFF9CFFD0FC08FA430CC6FA1B" box="[936,998,1433,1459]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2004.0">2004</number>
) revision and his attempt to define the taxonomic status of the various species, especially the new ones, lacks clarity. New species are either poorly illustrated or not even illustrated, and only large color photographs of the dorsal aspect are provided. These, however, are of little use in absence of detailed drawings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC1DA58FF9CFFD0FE98F9BB0EDEF8EB" blockId="8.[264,1324,433,1859]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
We went through Kovařík’ (
<number id="3DB6C87FFF9CFFD0FD25F9BB0DE3F9D3" box="[645,707,1633,1659]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2004.0">2004</number>
) monograph and attempted to compare our material with 
<taxonomicName id="4C7EA1DBFF9CFFD0FEE5F9530C03F90B" authority="Kovarik, 2004" authorityName="Kovarik" authorityYear="2004" box="[325,803,1673,1699]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Heterometrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nepalensis">
<emphasis id="B90A064AFF9CFFD0FEE5F9530D4BF90A" box="[325,619,1673,1698]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Heterometrus nepalensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFEFA7A9FF9CFFD0FDD4F9530C03F90B" author="Kovarik" box="[628,803,1673,1699]" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" refString="Kovarik, F. (2004) A review of the genus Heterometrus Ehrenberg, 1828, with descriptions of seven new species (Scorpiones, Scorpionidae). Euscorpius, 15, 1 - 60." type="journal article" year="2004">
Kovařík, 
<number id="3DB6C87FFF9CFFD0FD45F9530C03F90B" box="[741,803,1673,1699]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the first species to be found and described from 
<collectingCountry id="F3699AC8FF9CFFD0FEE9F96B0EB3F963" box="[329,403,1713,1739]" name="Nepal" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Nepal</collectingCountry>
. The male 
<typeStatus id="54C564FAFF9CFFD0FDB5F96B0D5FF963" box="[533,639,1713,1739]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">holotype</typeStatus>
, deposited in his personal collection was not available for examination, but comparative analysis of the original description, based mainly on color patterns and morphometric measurements, leads us to the conclusion that two different species are involved.
</paragraph>
